# Git Configuration Setup

1. git config --global user.name "<username>"
2. git config --global user.email "<your-email>"

3. git config --global user.name
4. git config --global user.email

5. git init
    it initializes a local repository/folder

6. git status
   => Displays the current status of files and commits in the git repo.
    Shows all the changes needed to be added and committed

7. git add .
    adds all the changes to the git repo

8. git commit -m "<commit-message>"

9. git remote add origin <remote-ssh-link>

10
Note .gitignore
    there are some files or folders that should not be committed or pushed to github
    such files and folders are kep in the .gitignore file.
